#: ../../source/process/training.rst:114
msgid "Meeting Etiquette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:116
msgid ""
"Inspired by Corey Hulen's blog article of `6 Annoying Things People Do "
"During Video Conferencing <http://hulen.com/video-conf-peevs/>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:118
msgid "Avoid responding to messages in chat while on a meeting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:120
msgid ""
"It can be distracting when someone tries to covertly respond to a "
"message. First, other people on call may hear your keyboard and notice "
"you’re looking somewhere else. Second, if they are in the same channel as"
" you, they can see the message ``[User] is typing...`` in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:121
msgid ""
"**Tip**: If you feel the need to respond immediately and are easily "
"distracted, set yourself to \"Do Not Disturb\" mode while in meetings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:123
msgid "Avoid answering calls or checking text messages on your cell phone:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:125
msgid ""
"**Tip**: Put your phone on silent and place it out of arm’s reach, face "
"down, so you don’t feel compelled to act."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:127
msgid "Display your video on a monitor with your camera:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:129
msgid ""
"If you have your video display on a second monitor, it may cause you to "
"look away from the camera, not looking at the camera when talking. It "
"almost feels like you’re talking to someone else in the room behind your "
"computer monitor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:130
msgid ""
"**Tip**: Either move your camera, or move your video window so they are "
"somewhat inline. Also remember to look towards the camera."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:132
msgid "Mute audio in large video conferences when not speaking:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:134
msgid ""
"When not muted, others can hear random noises, like a fan running or a "
"loud click-clack keyboard, which can be distracting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:135
msgid ""
"**Tip**: Set your Zoom meetings to be on mute by default via Zoom "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:137
msgid "Avoid fidgeting uncontrollably or spinning in your office chair:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:139
msgid ""
"**Tip** If you’re in a group meeting and not doing much talking, feel "
"free to stop your video."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:141
msgid "Avoid connecting with your computer but also dialing in via cell phone:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:143
msgid ""
"If you connect with your computer and dial in, there are two of you in "
"the meeting and the voice/video are not synced when you talk. In large "
"groups, there will be a random cell phone number that no one will know "
"who they are."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:144
msgid ""
"**Tip**: If you're having a bad internet connection and have to dial in, "
"exit the Zoom meeting on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:146
msgid ""
"When presenting, increase window zoom size or set Powerpoint slides to "
"presenter mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:148
msgid "Otherwise, the text on screen may be too hard for others to see."
msgstr ""

