#: ../../source/process/training.rst:763
msgid "Training"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:765
msgid ""
"At Mattermost, \"Learn, Master, Teach\" cycles are core to our culture. "
"You should be constantly growing and cross-training into new skills and "
"responsibilities, developing expertise, and then training your "
"replacement as you prepare to take on new challenges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:767
msgid ""
"Cross-training creates a culture of constant growth, protects against "
"single-points of failure, and challenges each of us to rise to our "
"fullest potential."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:771
msgid "Roles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:773
msgid ""
"The \"Learn, Master, Teach\" cycle happens in the context of roles. Roles"
" are sets of responsibility needed to achieve objectives. Roles aren't "
"necessarily job titles, for small projects, a developer might take on a "
"product manager role, or vice versa. Each team member has a \"primary "
"role\" and training should move people to mastery and teaching in that "
"role, before moving to the next role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:776
msgid "Developer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:778
msgid ""
"Developers are responsible for architecting and delivering software "
"improvements, and for technical leadership among the Mattermost "
"community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:781
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:781
msgid ""
"Developers are responsible for researching, analyzing, designing and "
"reviewing technical solutions to achieve functional requirements. "
"Solutions should thoroughly consider trade-offs and be evaluated based on"
" the effectiveness of the end implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:784
msgid "Delivery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:784
msgid ""
"Based on technical designs, developers estimate, implement, test, "
"maintain, review, debug and release software improvements in "
"collaboration with teammates. This includes working closely with product "
"managers to validate requirements and the output of designs and making "
"appropriate adjustments. The success of implementation is judged on the "
"end results achieved by the changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:787
msgid "Technical Community Leadership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:787
msgid ""
"As leading experts on Mattermost technology, developers support and "
"engage constantly with the broader Mattermost community to accelerate "
"adoption and to discover new ways to improve Mattermost software and "
"processes. This includes investigating and  supporting issues from users "
"and customers, reviewing and providing feedback on projects from "
"contributors, and understanding priorities, trends and patterns across "
"the community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:790
msgid "Product Managers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:792
msgid ""
"Product managers are responsible for aligning teams to strategic "
"priorities, leading and managing the product development process, and "
"working effectively with marketing to bring the full benefits of "
"Mattermost solutions to users and customers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:795
msgid "Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:795
msgid ""
"Every project and every team needs to align to strategic priorities and "
"focus on intended outcomes developed through a deep understanding of the "
"market, user, customers and competing products and services. Amid a flood"
" of compelling suggestions, opinions, and data, product managers must "
"find what's vital, and rally teams around a shared vision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:799
msgid "Product development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:798
msgid ""
"Product managers lead both the functional design process (user, customer "
"and competitor research, analysis, ideation, prioritization, functional "
"and user experience design, functional specification, user and customer "
"validation), and the software development process (ticketing, "
"prioritization, roadmap design, scheduling, sprint planning, triage, "
"functional verification, implementation validation with users and "
"customers, documentation, and release logistics)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:799
msgid ""
"It's the product manager's responsibility to see features shipped "
"predictably and at high quality through planning, attention to detail and"
" thoughtful persuasion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:802
msgid "Marketing connection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/training.rst:802
msgid ""
"Delivering benefits to users and customers based on product features is a"
" core responsibility of product managers, working in conjunction with "
"marketing to shape messaging and positioning and delivering collateral, "
"events, and user and customer discussions to support sales."
msgstr ""

